                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First off I would like to state that I have been a subscriber since december of 1999.  I like EQ.  I think it is and will be better than WoW or EQ2.
<br />

<br />
Ok, now to my questions and thoughts.
<br />

<br />
Your player base is not asking for another expansion.  We have to much as is, we simply want the problems worked out and let us all fully explore what we have.
<br />
We DO understand that mmorpgs are very complex and I'd say 90-95% of us have no problems forgiving and forgeting bugs and broken quests as long as they are fixed.
<br />

<br />
Now, a new expansion is coming, and even though I cannot imagine why, lets look at what you are going to add.
<br />

<br />

<br />
1. <span style="font-style: italic">Epic weapons are a result of completing an "epic quest." These hand-tailored quests will be available to all classes. The quest themselves will be a combination of solo, group and raid content. However, these weapons are being designed for people at the upper end of the level spectrum.
<br />

<br />
The weapons themselves will be unique in design. Additionally, the weapons will have specialized characteristics that set them apart from traditional weapons</span>
<br />

<br />
This looks like a plus, IF you do it right.  They <span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="text-decoration: underline">need</span></span> to be balanced.  Look at the old epics.  Some epics require many raids and multiple high mobs to kill ( warrior, shadowknight, bard) while others are relativly easy (cleric, rogue).  Some are still useful (off hand ranger, rogue, bard) while others are not (warrior, paladin).  
<br />
I am not even going to get into the berserker epic.
<br />

<br />
Secondly they need to be obtainable by more than time/elemental level guilds.  Should they be difficult? Yes. Should you need be in a raiding guild to get them? No.   Maybe have a alternete route, instead of killing XXX raid mob.  Have the brotherhood have the item for sale in ldon points, but to get it you have to prove your loyality by having so many points in various ldons.  Or perhaps by proving your loyality in otherways to the NPC besides raiding. Multiple quests to get the same item, I can't even tell you what this would mean to me as a player.   
<br />

<br />
2. <span style="font-style: italic">The level cap increase is being designed to allow players the ability to reach levels above 65. With the level cap increase, new items, spells and quests will be available</span>
<br />
This is iffy,  agian seems to be tailoring to your top 5% and not the rest of us.  Personally, I say add more level 65 content.  More BoT, more HoH.  Less GoD, less time.  Give all the 65's something to do, make quests that don't require loot from elemental planes.  Give us quests that we can do solo, that don't require farming. 
<br />
Also if you continue to snuff the casters by making spells harder and harder to get you will lose more of your fanbase.
<br />
As a enchanter I rely on my spells 100%, a warrior, a ranger, a beastlord do not.  You are crippling one set of classes but allowing the rest to fuction with little difficutly.
<br />

<br />
3.  <span style="font-style: italic">Guild Tribute System, Task System, Custom PC Titles , New Disciplines/AAs/Items/Spells/Quests/Tradeskills, Improved Graphics.</span>
<br />

<br />
Lumping these together because they will not make or break this expanson.
<br />
Improved graphics and guild tribute system along with the custom titles are all neat things, nothing to earthshatters.  But please, I don't know how many more deaths I can take because a mob is in the floor do to a graphic error.
<br />

<br />
The task system seems like a A+++ idea, I just hope it doesn't turn into a Tumpy Tonic means of leveling.
<br />

<br />
So to recap, I don't think you should have came out with a new expansion so quickly, but since it is coming.  Please don't ruin the game I love.
<br />

<br />
Llan 
<br />
65 Enchanter 
<br />
65 SK
<br />
54 Shaman
<br />
51 Warrior
<br />
Tunare Server[/u][/b]</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
